definition:
γῆ, γῆς, ἡ, 
 [in LXX for אֲדָמָה ,אֶרֶץ, etc. ;] 
   1. the earth, world: Luk.21:35, Act.1:8, Heb.11:13, Rev.3:10, al.; opposite to οὐρανός, Mat.5:18 11:25, Mrk.13:27, al. 
   2. land; 
  (a) opposite to sea or water: Mrk.4:1, Luk.5:3, Jhn.6:21, al.; 
   (b) as subject to cultivation: Mat.13:5, Mrk.4:8, Luk.13:7, Heb.6:7, al.; 
   (with) the ground: Mat.10:29, Mrk.8:6, Luk.24:5, Jhn.8:6, al.; 
   (d) a region, country: Luk.4:25, Rom.9:28, Jas.5:17; γῆ Ἰσραήλ, Mat.2:20, 21; Χαλδαίων, Act.7:4; ἡ Ἰουδαία γῆ, Jhn.3:22; with genitive of person(s), Act.7:3.
 (AS)
